The Eccentric Woodland is a forest south of Midgaard, beyond the Southern Wild Gate. It resists stable navigation. Paths shift between visits. Clearings change character from day to night. Landmarks vanish on return trips.

Named during the Lantern Reforms when survey clerks could not standardize southern routes past the ninth milestone. "Eccentric Woodland" was a registry label acknowledging ungovernable terrain.

Before paving of Midgaard's southern districts, shepherd-priests and bell walkers guided travelers through fog-prone hollows using bells and trust-based navigation.

Four factions contest the interior. Path Wardens sell navigation and protection along claimed routes. Ritual Houses maintain enclosed oath-bound groups that legitimate rank through dueling rooms and binding circles. Predator Bands mimic ritual forms to coerce compliance. Survivor Clusters inhabit burrows and clearings as temporary barter communities.

No faction controls the whole forest. Power is local, contingent, and theatrical. Midgaard governs only at the boundary — gate records are kept clean, interior incidents classified as variance events. The forest is an institutional blind spot no city office will absorb.

Path drift, contradictory witness accounts, and disappearing landmarks are consistent across all eras of patrol reports. The terrain resists repeatable pathing and standard registry systems.

